### File Structure
```
OnlineCourse/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── course_catalog.html
│   ├── course_details.html
│   ├── my_courses.html
│   ├── course_learning.html
│   ├── my_assignments.html
│   ├── submit_assignment.html
│   ├── certificates.html
│   └── user_profile.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   └── js/
│       └── scripts.js
│
└── data/
    ├── users.txt
    ├── courses.txt
    ├── enrollments.txt
    ├── assignments.txt
    ├── submissions.txt
    └── certificates.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python application file that handles routing, business logic, data file operations (reading/writing text files), and serves the web pages. It implements all required functionalities such as user session management, course browsing, enrollment, progress tracking, assignment submission, certificate generation, and profile updates.

- templates/
  Directory containing HTML template files for each of the nine pages defined in the requirements. These templates use placeholders to dynamically render data passed from app.py.

  - dashboard.html
    The Learning Dashboard page showing welcome message, enrolled courses, and navigation buttons.

  - course_catalog.html
    The Available Courses page with search input, course grid, and navigation controls.

  - course_details.html
    The Course Details page displaying course info and enrollment button.

  - my_courses.html
    The My Courses page listing enrolled courses with progress and continue learning buttons.

  - course_learning.html
    The Course Learning page showing lessons, lesson content, and controls to mark lessons complete.

  - my_assignments.html
    The My Assignments page displaying assignments table and submission buttons.

  - submit_assignment.html
    The Submit Assignment page with assignment info, text area for submission, and submit button.

  - certificates.html
    The My Certificates page showing earned certificates in a grid.

  - user_profile.html
    The My Profile page for viewing and editing user profile information.

- static/
  Directory for static assets like CSS and JavaScript files.

  - css/styles.css
    Stylesheet for consistent styling of all pages.

  - js/scripts.js
    JavaScript file for client-side interactivity such as button actions and form validations.

- data/
  Directory containing all local text files used for data storage as specified.

  - users.txt
    Stores user information (username, email, fullname).

  - courses.txt
    Stores course details.

  - enrollments.txt
    Stores enrollment records including progress and status.

  - assignments.txt
    Stores assignment details.

  - submissions.txt
    Stores assignment submissions and grading info.

  - certificates.txt
    Stores issued certificates for completed courses.
```
